
Overview of noun referee

The noun referee has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (1) referee, ref -- ((sports) the chief official (as in boxing or American football) who is expected to ensure fair play)
2. reviewer, referee, reader -- (someone who reads manuscripts and judges their suitability for publication)
3. referee -- (an attorney appointed by a court to investigate and report on a case)

Overview of verb referee

The verb referee has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                      
1. referee, umpire -- (be a referee or umpire in a sports competition)
2. referee, peer review -- (evaluate professionally a colleague's work)
